  "texts": [
    "This can be achieved, e.g.",
    "by combining scale-invariant and scale-variant features to devise a multi-scale CNN architecture (Van Noord and Postma 2017).",
    "Py et al. (2016) proposed an inception module that allows to use multiple scaled versions of the original image with different sizes as the input for CNN.",
    "By selecting different strides for each scale, the computed feature maps have the same size for all scales and can be concatenated to a single set of multi-scale features.",
    "The proposed method was shown to outperform the method with a single fixed-size input."
  ],
